Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #large pot{} of @salted water{}.

Chop the @potatoes{3}(peeled into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pot{}, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @milk{optional} or @water{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

Lay the @Irish chicken breast{320%grams} on a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Roast on the top shelf of the oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Trim the @carrots{2}(halved lengthways) and halve lengthways (unpeeled). Chop into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Place on a lined baking tray. Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste}, @sugar{1%tsp} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Enclose the @garlic{2}(whole cloves) in a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Roast the garlic parcel next to the carrots for ~{10%minutes} then remove from the oven.

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%grams}.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When hot, add the mushrooms and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Fry until browned, stirring occasionally, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @red wine jus{2%sachets} and a knob of @butter{to taste}. Simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} to loosen the sauce if required. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Remove from the heat and cover to keep warm.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork{}.

Stir the roasted garlic into the creamy mashed potato.

Slice the roasted chicken widthways.

Divide the chicken between #plates{}.

Serve the garlic mash and roast carrots alongside.

To finish, spoon the mushroom sauce over the chicken (reheating first if necessary).